.\" Manpage for gitls.
.\" Contact sven@siepermann.dev to correct errors or typos.
.TH GITLS 1 "2026-06-13" "gitls" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gitls \- inspect and act on multiple git repositories at once
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gitls
.RB [ fetch | pull ]
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ directory ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gitls
recursively scans
.I directory
(the current directory by default) for git repositories and prints a compact
status table: repository name, current branch, sync state relative to the
upstream remote, relative last\-commit time, and the working\-tree status
(staged, modified and untracked file counts).
.PP
Beyond the read\-only listing, it can act on every clean repository at once \(em
switch branches
.RB ( \-s ),
fetch
.RB ( fetch )
or fast\-forward pull
.RB ( pull )
\(em and a live watch mode
.RB ( \-w )
keeps the table on screen and lets you trigger those actions interactively.
.PP
Repositories are processed in parallel. The directories
.IR vendor , " node_modules"
and
.I .git
internals are skipped automatically.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B fetch
Fetch every repository from its
.I origin
remote and show the updated ahead/behind status. May be combined with
.BR \-s .
.TP
.B pull
Fast\-forward pull every clean repository. Repositories with staged or modified
files are skipped; diverged repositories are reported and never force\-merged.
.PP
A subcommand may appear before or after the options.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-s " branch"
Switch every clean repository to
.I branch
if it exists. A repository is switched only when it has no staged or modified
files. With
.BR fetch ,
a local tracking branch is created automatically from
.IB origin / branch
when the branch is not present locally. Cannot be combined with
.BR pull .
.TP
.BI \-d " n"
Maximum directory recursion depth (default: 5).
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-watch " [\fIn\fR]"
Watch mode: render the status table on the alternate screen and refresh it in
place every
.I n
seconds (default: 3). Interactive; see
.B WATCH MODE
below. Requires an interactive terminal on both stdin and stdout and cannot be
combined with
.BR fetch ", " pull " or " \-s .
.TP
.B \-\-dirty
List only repositories that are not both clean and in sync \(em those with
staged, modified or untracked files, commits ahead of or behind the remote, a
diverged branch, or a detached HEAD. The summary line still counts all scanned
repositories and notes how many were hidden.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-dirty
Show all repositories, overriding
.B dirty_only
from the configuration file for a single run.
.TP
.B \-a
Include hidden directories (those whose name begins with a dot) in the scan.
.TP
.B \-v
Verbose: list every repository in the fetch/pull/switch summaries, not just the
ones that changed.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable ANSI colour output.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.SH WATCH MODE
In watch mode the table is redrawn in place at a fixed interval on the
terminal's alternate screen buffer, so the scrollback is left untouched. The
terminal is always restored on exit, including on
.B SIGINT
and
.BR SIGTERM .
The following keys act on the whole tree without leaving the view:
.TP
.B f
Fetch all repositories from
.IR origin .
.TP
.B p
Fast\-forward pull all clean repositories.
.TP
.B s
Open the branch picker, then switch all clean repositories to the chosen branch.
The picker lists the recently active branches across all repositories, most
recent first; type to filter, use the arrow keys to move the selection and
Tab or Enter to choose. Esc cancels.
.TP
.B r
Refresh now without waiting for the interval.
.TP
.BR q ", Ctrl\-C"
Quit.
.PP
The automatic refresh and the
.B r
key re\-scan locally only; they do not fetch. The
.B f
and
.B p
keys require the
.BR git (1)
binary.
.SH STATUS INDICATORS
.TP
.B \(ti
Clean working tree.
.TP
.BI \(bu N
.I N
staged files.
.TP
.BI \(mu N
.I N
modified (unstaged) files.
.TP
.BI ? N
.I N
untracked files.
.TP
.BI \(ua N
.I N
commits ahead of the remote.
.TP
.BI \(da N
.I N
commits behind the remote.
.TP
.B \(ua\fIN\fB\(da\fIM\fR
Diverged by
.I N
ahead and
.I M
behind.
.TP
.B \(==
In sync with the remote.
.TP
.B ?
No remote configured.
.SH CONFIGURATION
On start
.B gitls
reads
.I ~/.gitlsrc
(or the file named by
.BR GITLS_CONFIG ).
Command\-line flags always override the configuration. Recognised keys:
.TP
.B default_dir
Directory to scan when none is given on the command line. Passing an explicit
directory (including \(lq.\(rq) always overrides this.
.TP
.B max_depth
Maximum directory recursion depth (default: 5).
.TP
.B skip_dirs
Comma\-separated list of directory names to skip; glob patterns are supported.
.TP
.B watch_interval
Default refresh interval in seconds for
.BR \-w " (default: 3)."
.TP
.B dirty_only
Set to
.B true
or
.B 1
to filter to dirty repositories by default, as if
.B \-\-dirty
were given. Override for a single run with
.BR \-\-no\-dirty .
.TP
.B no_color
Set to
.B true
or
.B 1
to disable colour output.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GITLS_CONFIG
Path to an alternate configuration file, used instead of
.IR ~/.gitlsrc .
.TP
.B COLUMNS
Consulted as a fallback for the terminal width when it cannot be queried.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.gitlsrc
Per\-user configuration file.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success and a non\-zero value on a usage error or a failure to
initialise libgit2 or resolve the scan directory.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B gitls ~/projects
Show the status table for every repository under
.IR ~/projects .
.TP
.B gitls \-w ~/projects
Watch
.I ~/projects
live, refreshing every three seconds.
.TP
.B gitls \-\-dirty ~/projects
List only the repositories that need attention.
.TP
.B gitls \-s main ~/projects
Switch every clean repository to the
.I main
branch.
.TP
.B gitls fetch \-s feature\-x ~/projects
Fetch, then switch to
.IR feature\-x ,
creating a local tracking branch where it only exists on the remote.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git (1)
